  "texts": [
    "AI models trained predominantly on Western data may fail to represent the sensory preferences of diverse populations, resulting in biased recommendations or the marginalization of non-Western flavor traditions.",
    "This issue extends beyond technical concerns to touch on the ethics of cultural representation and respect.",
    "Inclusive training data, participatory design involving local communities, and culturally adaptive AI frameworks are essential for ensuring that new technologies reflect the richness of global sensory diversity.",
    "Neglecting these aspects could reinforce cultural homogenization and reduce consumer trust, particularly in multicultural and international markets.",
    "Finally, public understanding and transparency must be central to any ethical framework."
  ],
